/*
 ============================================================================
 File        : transmitter.ino
 Project     : DIY Smart Band using ESP32 + LoRa + Firebase
 Author      : Sathyanath L
 College     : Rajalakshmi Engineering College
 Description :
    This program runs on the ESP32 transmitter node of the DIY Smart Band.

 Hardware Used:
    • ESP32 DevKit V1
    • SX1278 LoRa Module (433MHz)
    • MAX30105 Heart Rate Sensor
    • NEO-6M GPS Module
    • Push Button (SOS)
    • Li-Po Battery

 Features:
    ✓ Reads Heart Rate from MAX30105
    ✓ Reads GPS Coordinates from NEO-6M
    ✓ Sends sensor data using LoRa
    ✓ Supports SOS Push Button
    ✓ Low-power wearable transmitter

 Communication:
    LoRa Frequency : 433 MHz
    Data Format :
        HR:91,
        Lat:12.971652,
        Lon:80.220317,
        Sat:7,
        Alt:15.4,
        SOS:0,
        T:658301

 Pin Connections
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 LoRa Module
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 SCK    -> GPIO18
 MISO   -> GPIO19
 MOSI   -> GPIO23
 NSS    -> GPIO5
 RST    -> GPIO14
 DIO0   -> GPIO26

 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 MAX30105
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 SDA    -> GPIO21
 SCL    -> GPIO22
 VIN    -> 3.3V
 GND    -> GND

 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 GPS (NEO-6M)
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 TX     -> GPIO16
 RX     -> GPIO17
 VCC    -> 3.3V
 GND    -> GND

 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Push Button
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Button -> GPIO32
 Other  -> GND

 Libraries Required
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 LoRa by Sandeep Mistry
 TinyGPS++
 SparkFun MAX3010x Sensor Library
 heartRate.h

 ============================================================================
*/
